        "rich_text_tM3jbz": {
          "type": "rich_text",
          "name": "Understanding The Basics of Ring Sizes",
          "settings": {
            "content": "<h2>Understanding The Basics of Ring Sizes </h2><p>Before you measure your ring size, it helps to understand what a ring size is. A ring size is the inner diameter or the circumference of the ring; it reflects how wide the ring should be to sit well on your finger. Different countries use different measuring systems such as some countries follow a ring size chart in cm. For example, India uses a scale between 6-30, while the European system uses millimetre based numbers, and the UK and Australia have an alphabetical system. When shopping from a global brand, knowing this helps because even the tiniest difference in millimetres can decide if the ring is of the right size or not. Precision in ring size is critical, which is why a conversion chart helps.<br/><br/></p>",
            "custom_id": "basics"
          }
        },
